primaryOutcomes.description:
Pericarditis recurrence is defined as the occurrence of at least two of the following signs:

* at least 1 day of pericarditis pain ≥ 4 (on the 11 point numerical rating scale (NRS)) (without any other potential causes for the increase in the pain intensity);
* at least one CRP value ≥ 1 mg/dL (without any other potential causes for the C-reactive protein (CRP elevation));
* new or progression of existing pericardial effusion during the diastole as demonstrated by echocardiography;
* evidence of new widespread ST-elevation (ST segment / T wave ratio in lead v6 \> 0.25) or PR depression on electrocardiogram (ECG).

Each sign can occur either on the same day or separated by no more than 7 days from another sign.
